This paper is about developing a general knowledge learning engine for chatbots, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and knowledge representation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers topics related to natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also proposes a novel technique called lifelong interactive learning and inference (LiLi) to solve the open-world knowledge base completion problem, which involves machine learning and inference. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also discusses the limitations of existing chatbots and proposes a solution to overcome them, which is related to information retrieval and knowledge representation. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another likely category. Finally, the paper proposes a technique that involves interactive learning and inference, which is related to human-computer interaction. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possible category.
